    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "For example, with Radar dome infiltration, you can do something like: (1) I don't know what it does now, (2) Enemy Units command (like the effect obtained on RA YR when creating a psichic radar, that you can see enemy where are moving/attacking, (3) Gas beacons or Player radar alert when the enemy place a bombing order, (4) You can permanently see the area around an enemy unit or to all the units created by a particular structure (es. an airstrip), with the same concept used for the Firestorm limpet drone.\n\nIf you infiltrate an enemy allied research center, you can see all their units moving (not just place-holder icons), if you infiltrate enemy superweapons you can booby trap them (if a chronosphere, when the enemy use it, it explodes instantly, if an enemy nuclear silo, it explode causing a nuclear detonation etc.)...\n\nThis keeps the player to continue on infiltration and the enemy to use dogs and check for potential base penetration points, more actively.\n"
